          "text": "Good - `trace_column()` doesn't exist in the actual code. Only referenced in TODO.md and CHANGELOG.md. Now I have enough to give a proper verdict on each item.\n\nHere's my analysis:\n\n---\n\n### Task 1 (P0): Fixed-Point Bounds Checking Gap -- PHANTOM BUG\n\nThe TODO claims `MapIsWall()` gets called without bounds checking in the fixed-point path. Wrong. Look at `raycaster_data.h:14-17`:\n\n```c\nstatic inline bool MapIsWall(uint8_t tileX, uint8_t tileY)\n{\n    if (tileX >= MAP_X - 1 || tileY >= MAP_Y - 1)\n        return true;\n```\n\n`MapIsWall` itself has the bounds check. When `tileX` is uint8_t and wraps from 0-1 to 255, that's >= 31 (MAP_X-1), so it returns true (wall). The \"unsafe\" scenario described cannot happen. The float version's `RayCasterFloatIsWall()` check for negative coordinates before uint8_t cast is defense-in-depth, not a correctness fix the fixed path is missing.\n\nVerdict: **Remove or demote to P3 as a style/clarity note** (\"add explicit comment explaining why uint8_t wrap is safe\").\n\n### Task 2 (P0): Precalculator Silent Truncation -- VALID but MISRANKED\n\nThe `fminf()` clamping at `precalculator.c:56` is intentional and correct -- tan approaches infinity near 90 degrees, and the lookup table format is uint16_t. A diagnostic warning during table generation would be nice for development, but this is not a correctness bug. No user-visible behavior depends on whether `tan[255]` is 65535 or something larger.\n\nVerdict: **Demote to P3.** It's a build-quality improvement, not a correctness issue.\n\n### Task 3 (P1): Float Tracer DDA Redesign -- VALID\n\nAccurate description. The float tracer mirrors the fixed-point engine's intercept-based approach with separate H/V passes and uses `g_deltaAngle` from the precalculator. A DDA + camera-plane rewrite would make it a true standalone reference. Well-scoped, references exist in `externals/cub3d`.\n\n### Task 4 (P1): Runtime Map Configuration -- VALID\n\nCurrently maps are c